<section class="section" id="episodes" aria-labelledby="episodes-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-intro">
      <span class="label">Latest Episodes</span>
      <h2 id="episodes-heading">Recent Episodes of The Law Firm Growth Show</h2>
      <p>Each episode covers a specific growth strategy in depth, with real examples, actionable steps, and expert insights from the team behind Dominate Law.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px;">
      
      <article class="episode-card">
        <div class="episode-num">EP 01</div>
        <div class="episode-body">
          <h3>How Top Law Firms Dominate Google in 2026</h3>
          <p>The 3 types of SEO every law firm must master, plus a deep dive into Google Business Profile optimization and the 5 most common SEO mistakes that cost attorneys thousands of lost leads every month.</p>
          <div class="episode-meta">
            <span class="episode-tag">SEO</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">⏱ 42 min</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">📅 March 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="episode-card">
        <div class="episode-num">EP 02</div>
        <div class="episode-body">
          <h3>The Review Strategy That Builds Trust Before the First Call</h3>
          <p>How to build a systematic review generation process, what to say to get clients to leave detailed 5-star reviews, and how to respond to negative reviews without making them worse.</p>
          <div class="episode-meta">
            <span class="episode-tag">Reputation</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">⏱ 38 min</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">📅 March 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="episode-card">
        <div class="episode-num">EP 03</div>
        <div class="episode-body">
          <h3>Social Media for Law Firms: What Actually Works in 2026</h3>
          <p>The 4 content types that drive engagement for attorneys, which platforms to prioritize, and a realistic content schedule for busy lawyers who don't have a marketing team.</p>
          <div class="episode-meta">
            <span class="episode-tag">Social Media</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">⏱ 45 min</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">📅 February 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="episode-card">
        <div class="episode-num">EP 04</div>
        <div class="episode-body">
          <h3>Email Marketing for Attorneys: From Lead to Signed Client</h3>
          <p>Building a 10-email nurture sequence, the ideal timing between emails, and the subject line formulas that get lawyers' emails opened in a crowded inbox.</p>
          <div class="episode-meta">
            <span class="episode-tag">Email Marketing</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">⏱ 35 min</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">📅 February 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="episode-card">
        <div class="episode-num">EP 05</div>
        <div class="episode-body">
          <h3>Panel Events That Fill Your Calendar with Qualified Leads</h3>
          <p>How to plan, promote, and host a panel event that generates 20+ consultations — including the exact promotional timeline, speaker selection process, and post-event follow-up system.</p>
          <div class="episode-meta">
            <span class="episode-tag">Lead Gen</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">⏱ 50 min</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">📅 January 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="episode-card">
        <div class="episode-num">EP 06</div>
        <div class="episode-body">
          <h3>Building a Referral Network That Works While You Sleep</h3>
          <p>Mapping your referral ecosystem, the monthly check-in system that keeps referrals flowing, and how to turn every new client into a source of future referrals.</p>
          <div class="episode-meta">
            <span class="episode-tag">Referrals</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">⏱ 41 min</span>
            <span class="episode-duration">📅 January 2026</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

